The paper deals with communication over noisy channels and the problem of ensuring covertness, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of typical sets, which are commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the fundamental limits of covert and secret communications, which falls under the Security and Privacy (cs.SI) sub-category.
